Melania and Donald Trump send their warm wishes to Jewish people around the world as they begin celebrating Hanukkah. They highlight the story of the Maccabees reclaiming the Holy Temple and the miracle of the menorah burning for eight nights. They emphasize that freedom and justice will always prevail over hate and oppression. The Trumps also express their strong support for the United States' relationship with Israel and the right to worship freely. They conclude by wishing everyone a memorable and blessed celebration filled with happiness, fellowship, and renewed faith.